Next, cover `UserService`. It has two distinct responsibilities:

1. Reading and mapping a user with sales points.
2. Creating a user and synchronizing it with Ping.

There are also a few production-code improvements worth making before finalizing the tests.

## 1. Parameterize null and blank `userId`

Sonar may flag separate null/blank tests as duplicated, so use one parameterized test:

```java
@ParameterizedTest
@NullSource
@ValueSource(strings = {"", " "})
void shouldRejectMissingUserId(String userId) {
    IllegalArgumentException exception = assertThrows(
            IllegalArgumentException.class,
            () -> service.getUserById(userId)
    );

    assertEquals(
            "userId must not be blank",
            exception.getMessage()
    );

    verifyNoInteractions(userRepository);
}
```

