## 3. Important optimization: remove hardcoded authorization data

The current mapper contains:

```java
response.setRelatedDealer(
        new RelatedPartyResponse("DLR001", "Dealer 1")
);

response.setRelatedZoneManager(
        new RelatedPartyResponse("ZM001", "Zone Manager 1")
);

response.setRoles(
        List.of("SELLER", "DEALER")
);
```

This should not remain hardcoded in production. Every user will otherwise receive the same dealer, zone manager and roles.

Until the real repository queries are implemented, prefer empty values:

```java
response.setRelatedDealer(null);
response.setRelatedZoneManager(null);
response.setRoles(List.of());
```

Or, more cleanly, do not set them until real data is available.

Eventually these should come from:

```java
relationshipRepository
roleRepository
organizationRepository
```

or an equivalent query that returns the actual tenant-scoped data.

## 4. Protect the database column from long Ping errors

`UserSynchronizationService` limits Ping errors to 2,000 characters, but `UserService.createUser(...)` currently appears to store the full message:

```java
savedUser.setPingLastError(exception.getMessage());
```

Use the same protection here:

```java
private static final int MAXIMUM_PING_ERROR_LENGTH = 2000;

private String limitErrorMessage(String message) {
    if (message == null) {
        return null;
    }

    return message.length() <= MAXIMUM_PING_ERROR_LENGTH
            ? message
            : message.substring(
                    0,
                    MAXIMUM_PING_ERROR_LENGTH
            );
}
```

Then:

```java
savedUser.setPingLastError(
        limitErrorMessage(exception.getMessage())
);
```

Better still, extract Ping synchronization into one shared service so `UserService` and `UserSynchronizationService` do not duplicate the same status/error-handling logic.

## 5. Avoid logging the full user object

This line may expose personal information:

```java
log.debug("user details {}", user);
```

The entity can contain email, phone number and potentially other sensitive fields. Prefer:

```java
log.debug(
        "User retrieved successfully for userId={}",
        userId
);
```

The same applies to:

```java
log.debug("user details {}", userResponse);
```

Log identifiers and status, not the full user or response object.
